>
> thanks for the quick reply.
>
> i made a simple change to the ARCReader class and then did 'maven 
> dist:build' which
> seems to take forever.  here's the output.  sure would be nice not to 
> have to wait for all the
> tests to complete just to try out my mod.
>
> 'maven jar:jar' seems to be faster but still runs the tests.
>
The 'dist' target does a bunch of packaging (Builds two webapps, 
generates documentation, builds src and bin packages).  Its probably not 
what you want.

The 'jar' target makes more sense for what you are trying to do.  Yeah, 
it runs the junit tests each time.  Thats the default for the maven jar 
target.  Do the following if you want to eliminate the running of unit 
tests:
